           SHORT="VideoLAN client multimedia player"
cat << EOF
The VideoLAN Client (vlc) is a multi-plateform multimedia player. It can read DVDs, VCDs, MPEG and DivX files from a file and from a satellite card under Linux, Windows, Mac OS X, BeOS, BSD, Solaris, QNX, iPaq... It can also read a stream from a network, sent by the VideoLAN Server or another source. The stream can be MPEG 2 TS in UDP or HTTP packets unicasted or multicasted on an IPv4 or IPv6 network.
Supports X11/XVideo, SDL, Linux framebuffer, OSS, esound, arts, alsa, GNOME, GTK+, Qt, KDE.
EOF
